erican drama films]]\n[[Category:American silent short films]]\n[[Category:American black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by D. W. Griffith]]\n{{1900s-short-drama-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1909 film}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=February 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = A Burglar's Mistake\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[D. W. Griffith]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = D. W. Griffith\n| starring       = [[Harry Solter]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = [[G. W. Bitzer]]<br>[[Arthur Marvin]]\n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|1909|3|25}}\n| runtime        = 10 minutes (one [[Reel#Motion picture terminology|reel]])\n| country        = United States\n| language       = Silent\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''A Burglar's Mistake''''' is a 1909 American [[silent film|silent]] [[short film|short]] [[drama film]] directed by [[D. W. Griffith]].<ref name=\"silentera\">{{cite web |url=http://www.silentera.com/PSFL/data/B/BurglarsMistake1909.html |title=A Burglar's Mistake |accessdate=February 13, 2015 |work=Silent Era}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Harry Solter]] as Henry Newman\n* [[Charles Inslee]] as Dick Folsom\n* [[Marion Leonard]] as Mrs. Newman\n* [[Adele DeGarde]] as One of the Children\n* [[Robert Harron]] as The Messenger\n* [[Raymond Hatton]] as At Folsom's / Secretary (unconfirmed)\n* [[Arthur V. Johnson]] as Policeman\n* [[David Miles (actor)|David Miles]] as At Folsom's\n* [[Owen Moore]] as At Folsom's\n* [[Herbert Prior]] as Policeman\n* [[Gertrude Robinson]] as One of the Children\n* [[Mack Sennett]] as At Folsom's / Policeman\n* [[Dorothy West (actress)|Dorothy West]] as One of the Children\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0000819|A Burglar's Mistake}}\n*{{AFI film|id=35515|title=A Burglar's Mistake}}\n*{{Tcmdb title|id=509442|title=A Burglar's Mistake}}\n{{D. W. Griffith |state=collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTS